Iske bina to khane ka maza hi adhura hai, batao kis kiska favourite hai Kairi ka Achar?🥹🥭
We make it every year at home during the ongoing season and itna tasty banta hai ki jitna bhi dalo 4-5 months se zyada nhi chalta!😌🫠
.
.
Ingredients-
🔺5kg Kachi Kairi/ Raw Mango
🔺3 litre Sarson ka tel/ Mustard oil (approx)
🔺1 cup Lahsun/ Garlic cloves 
🔺1/2 cup Lal mirch powder/ Red chilli powder (or acc to taste)
🔺1 cup Chana Dal/ split chickpea lentil
🔺1/2 cup Sauf/ Fennel seeds
🔺1/4th cup Rai/ Mustard seeds
🔺1/4th cup Pili Sarso/ Yellow mustard seeds
🔺1/2 cup Methi dana/ Fenugreek seeds
🔺Salt to taste (approx 3/4th cup)
🔺1tbsp Haldi/ Turmeric 
🔺1tbsp Hing/ Asafoetida 
.
Wash Raw Mangoes nicely and let them dry, now chop each “kairi” into 5-6 small pieces.
Sprinkle some Turmeric and Salt over the chopped pieces, mix and spread on a sheet.
Let it dry under fan for 3-4 hours and then mix all the ingredients mentioned above.
Store it well in a glass container or pickle jar, it will take about 15-17 days to get ready completely.
.
.

Have you ever tried Maharashtrian Zunka?😋😍
Though similar dish is prepared using almost the same recipe in many parts of the country but the texture is different, some prefer it dry, some prefer it with semi- thick consistency while others prefer a slightly runny consistency, completely a personal choice. 
My favourite has to be this Maharashtrian Zunka, has good spice with the crunch of onions and hint of lemon! 
.
Ingredients-
🔺2tbsp Besan/ Gram flour 
🔺1 Pyaz/ Onion (finely chopped)
🔺1-2 Hari mirch/ Green chilli
🔺7-8 Lahsun/ Garlic cloves 
🔺1/2tbsp Tel/ Oil
🔺1/2tsp Jeera/ Cumin seeds
🔺1/2tsp Rai/ Mustard seeds
🔺Pinch of Hing/ Asafoetida 
🔺1/2tsp Lal mirch powder/ Red chilli powder 
🔺1/4th tsp Haldi/ Turmeric 
🔺Salt to taste
🔺Juice of 1/2 Lemon
🔺Dhaniya patti/ Coriander leaves 
.
This quantity is enough to serve 1-2.
.
.
